25|$|In 2005 and 2006, Second Life {{began to}} receive {{significant}} media attention, including {{a cover story}} on BusinessWeek magazine featuring <b>the</b> <b>virtual</b> <b>world</b> and Second Life avatar Anshe Chung. By that time, Anshe Chung had become Second Lifes poster child and symbol for the economic opportunities that <b>the</b> <b>virtual</b> <b>world</b> offers to its residents. At the same time, the service saw a period of exponential growth of its user base.|$|E
