25|$|The spell, {{intended}} to last only seconds and function {{only within the}} new area of Zul'Gurub, soon spread across <b>the</b> <b>virtual</b> <b>world</b> by way of an oversight that allowed pets and minions to take the affliction out of its intended confines. By both accidental and purposeful intent, a pandemic ensued that quickly killed lower-level characters and drastically changed normal gameplay, as players did {{what they could do}} to avoid infection. Despite measures such as programmer-imposed quarantines, and the players' abandoning of densely populated cities (or even just not playing the game), it lasted until a combination of patches and resets of <b>the</b> <b>virtual</b> <b>world</b> finally controlled the spread.|$|E
